title_full:
Edward George

            —
            The Strangeness of Dub

label: SFX
description:
Berlin's Zoë Mc Pherson refracts sonic psychedelia into precarious dancefloor experiments on 'Pitch Blender', leaning into a bass-heavy multi-dimensional sound that's somewhere between aya, Amazondotcom, Ani Klang, and Metrist. Essential gear.

title_full:
Conrad Pack / DJ Gonz / Leeway

            —
            Higher Reaction Sound

label: Worship
description:
D.K’s Worship label returns with a set of dank dembow x UKB hybrids on the line between ruder Downwards, ANA, early DMZ and Youth stylings, from Parisian lynchpin Louis Vial, aka Eszaid.

‘Encircled Earth’ taps into the Photek continuum on a downtempo set of neon-lit advanced/ardkore variations that sound something like Gescom via DMZ. 'Indraic Cut'... more

description:
